edirects here for the bus service in the british cities cambridge peterborough preston and gloucester see stagecoach group for the car see volkswagen citi golf citigroup inc citigroup headquarters in lower manhattan type public company traded as nyse c sp  component sp  component industry banking financial services predecessor citicorp travelers group founded june    years ago  headquarters  greenwich street new york new york  area served worldwide key people michael e oneill chairman michael corbat ceo james forese president products credit cards retail banking commercial bank investment banking private banking financial analysis revenue us billion  operating income us billion  net income us billion  total assets us trillion  total equity us billion  number of employees   subsidiaries citibank grupo financiero banamex citimortgage citibranded cards citi private bank citibank india citi securities  banking citigroup global markets japan salomon big sedna finance capital ratio   website citigroupcom citigroup inc or citi stylized as citi and pronounced like city is an american multinational investment banking and financial services corporation headquartered in manhattan new york city the company was formed by the merger of banking giant citicorp and financial conglomerate travelers group in  however travelers was spun off from the company in  citigroup now owns citicorp holding company for citibank and several international subsidiaries citigroup ranks th on the list of largest banks in the united states by assets and is one of the big four banks in the united states alongside jpmorgan chase bank of america and wells fargo in  citigroup ranked th in size on the fortune  list in addition to us money managers its largest shareholders include prince alwaleed bin talal of the saudi royal family and investors from abu dhabi and singapore citigroup has over  million customer accounts and does business in more than  countries citigroup has  employees although it had  employees at its height before the financial crisis of  citigroup suffered huge losses during the financial crisis of  and was rescued in november  in a massive stimulus package by the us government contents  current operations  history  citicorp –  travelers group –  ownership of salomon brothers –  merger of citicorp and travelers –  spinoff of travelers   subprime mortgage crisis   collapse  us government intervention   creation of citi holdings   sale of morgan stanley smith barney   return to profitability denationalization   expansion of retail banking operations   expansion of credit card operations   federal reserve stress tests –  spinoff of napier park global capital   downsizing of consumer banking unit    onwards  offices  new york city  naming rights to citi field  chicago  regulatory action lawsuits and arbitration  enron worldcom and global crossing bankruptcies  criticism  alleged money laundering by raul salinas  conflicts of interest on investment research  citigroup proprietary government bond trading scandal of   plutonomy report  tarp funding  terra securities scandal  allegations of theft from customer accounts  potential restructuring and liquidation by regulators  shareholder rejection of executive compensation plan  accusations of futures market manipulation  communications  lobbying  public and governmental relations  see also  references  further reading  external links current operationsedit a citi private bank office citigroup is the holding company for the following divisions citigroup global markets inc citigroup global markets limited uk and citigroup global markets japan  broker dealers including one of  primary dealers in united states treasury securities citis institutional clients group icg offers investment and corporate banking services and products for companies governments institutions and ultra highnetworth investors icg consists of the following five main divisions capital markets origination is focused on the capitalraising needs such as public offerings private placements and special purpose acquisition companies corporate  investment banking provides strategic and financing products and advisory services to multinational and local corporations financial institutions governments and privately held businesses in more than  countries it also provides client services such as mergers  acquisitions advice and underwriting of initial public offerings markets  securities services includes investor services and direct custody and clearing hedge fund and private equity servicing and issuer businesses it provides financial products through underwriting sales  trading of a range of investment assets products offered include servicing of equities commodities credit futures foreign exchange fx emerging markets g rates municipals prime financebrokerage services and securitized markets such as collateralized debt obligations and mortgagebacked securities its citi research team provides equity and fixed income research company sector economic and geographic market analysis and productspecific analysis for citis individual and institutional clients its flagship research reports include the following portfolio strategist bond market roundup us economics weekly international market roundup global economic outlook  strategy and the global equity strategist citi private bank advises professional investors ultra highnetworth individuals and families and lawyers throughout the world it uses an open architecture network of more than  private bankers and investment professionals across  countries and jurisdictions to provide clients access to global investment opportunities it has over  billion in assets under management the minimum net worth requirement is  million in liquid assets and is waived for only law firm groups and other clients under special circumstances citibank private bank treasury and trade solutions tts provides cash management trade and securities services to companies governments and other institutions in the us and more than  countries tts intermediates more than  trillion in global transactions daily it has over  trillion assets under custody about  billion in average liability balances serves  of worlds fortune  companies and  of the worlds fortune  companies and has  regional processing centers worldwide using global processes institutions use tts to support their treasury operations with global solutions for payments collections liquidity and investments by working in partnership with export credit agencies and development banks it also sells supply chain financing products as well as medium and longterm global financing programs across multiple industries clients doing business with citi in  or more countries generate more than  of transaction services total revenues grupo financiero banamex  the second largest bank in mexico it serves about  million clients citicorp  the holding company for citibank as well as several international banks citicorp contains two core businesses global consumer banking and institutional clients group citibank retail banking encompasses citis global branch network branded citibank citibank has more than  branches in the world and holds more than  billion in deposits citibank is the th largest retail bank in the united states based on deposits and it has citibank branded branches in countries throughout the world with the exception of mexico which is under a separate subsidiary called banamex citibank offers checking and savings accounts small business and commercial banking and personal wealth management among its services citibank offers citigold services worldwide to mass affluent clients with at least us in liquid assets in certain markets citigold select is available for clients with at least us in liquid assets its highest level of service citigold private client is for highnetworth individuals with at least – million in liquid assets depending on the market region and offers access to investments and ideas from cit