any for citibank and several international subsidiaries citigroup ranks th on the list of largest banks in the united states by assets and is one of the big four banks in the united states alongside jpmorgan chase bank of america and wells fargo in  citigroup ranked th in size on the fortune  list in addition to us money managers its largest shareholders include prince alwaleed bin talal of the saudi royal family and investors from abu dhabi and singapore citigroup has over  million customer accounts and does business in more than  countries citigroup has  employees although it had  employees at its height before the financial crisis of  citigroup suffered huge losses during the financial crisis of  and was rescued in november  in a massive stimulus package by the us government contents  current operations  history  citicorp –  travelers group –  ownership of salomon brothers –  merger of citicorp and travelers –  spinoff of travelers   subprime mortgage crisis   collapse  us government intervention   creation of citi holdings   sale of morgan stanley smith barney   return to profitability denationalization   expansion of retail banking operations   expansion of credit card operations   federal reserve stress tests –  spinoff of napier park global capital   downsizing of consumer banking unit    onwards  offices  new york city  naming rights to citi field  chicago  regulatory action lawsuits and arbitration  enron worldcom and global crossing bankruptcies  criticism  alleged money laundering by raul salinas  conflicts of interest on investment research  citigroup proprietary government bond trading scandal of   plutonomy report  tarp funding  terra securities scandal  allegations of theft from customer accounts  potential restructuring and liquidation by regulators  shareholder rejection of executive compensation plan  accusations of futures market manipulation  communications  lobbying  public and governmental relations  see also  references  further reading  exter